# Kubernetes Delivery

- Keep containers non-root, minimal, immutable, and compatible with read-only filesystems.
- Set resource requests, memory limits, probes, and graceful termination for each workload.
- Grant the worker only the Kubernetes verbs and namespaces required by implemented behavior.
- Keep API and web service accounts from receiving Kubernetes credentials by default.
- Put configurable deployment behavior in Helm values and validate public values with a schema.
- Never place credentials or cluster-specific values in tracked files.
- Keep `docker compose up --build --watch` as the complete local-stack entry point.
- Give Compose services health checks and use health-based dependency conditions.
- Keep development-only tools containerized and pin every external image and tool version.
- Keep kind and Tilt behavior representative of Helm deployment.
- Pin deployable image tags in release configuration; use `dev` only for local Tilt workflows.
- Validate charts with `helm lint` and `helm template` through Nx.
